name: printed wiring board production, through-hole mounted, unspecified, Pb free | printed wiring board, through-hole mounted, unspecified, Pb free | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10/documentation

This dataset represents 1 kg of an unspecified, through-hole mounted, PWB used in electronic devices. Main data are based on literature and own dismantling activities,  for the PWB of a television and of a power supply unit of a Intel PII desktop PC . Infrastructure and production efforts are based on own assumptions.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

From reception of solder materials at the factory gate.

This dataset includes component input and production efforts (incl. PWB waste due to failure in mounting) for the production of an unspecified, through-hole mounted, PWB, using Pb-free solder material.
